cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a framework for compressing state-of-the-art object detection models, specifically Single Shot MultiBox Detector (SSD), using sparsity induction, filter selection, and filter pruning. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques and model compression, which are common topics in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of sparsity statistics and filter pruning also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed framework on multiple datasets and comparison with other methods suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
